  'Early Jaguar alloy wheel design from the 1960s-1970s era. Part number 4010512 indicates this was an original equipment wheel for classic Jaguar models. The Super spoke design featured multiple spokes in a classic pattern typical of period European alloy wheels. These wheels were offered as alternatives to wire wheels on various Jaguar models including the E-Type, S-Type, and early XJ6. Documentation is limited for this specific design, suggesting it may have been a lower-production or early variant. The wheel utilized Jaguar''s standard 5x108mm bolt pattern and 63.4mm center bore that was consistent across their classic range.',
