  'BMW Style 26 ''Ellipsoid-Styling'' wheels manufactured by Cromodora Wheels in Italy. Original equipment for multiple BMW chassis. The 16" variant (7x16 ET46) was standard on most applications except M3 and 330 models. The 17" variant came in staggered fitments (8x17 ET20 front, 9x17 ET22 rear) primarily for sportier applications. Known for their distinctive multi-spoke ellipsoid design that creates an optical illusion of depth. Production spanned from early 1990s through 2000s across various BMW model ranges.',
