  'Originally exclusive to the BMW M3 CSL (2003-2004, 1,383 units produced). Later renamed to Style 163 M Cross Spoke when made available as part of the Competition Package (ZCP) for regular E46 M3s starting in 2005. Manufactured by BBS using flow-forming technology for lightweight construction. The CSL was BMW''s track-focused variant with extensive weight reduction, producing 360 hp and featuring these wheels as part of its performance package. These wheels became highly sought after for their combination of lightweight construction and iconic CSL heritage.',
