  'BMW Style 47 ''Double Spoke'' was a popular OEM wheel option across multiple BMW platforms in the mid-1990s through early 2000s. Excluded from M3 models (330 and M3 noted as exceptions). The twin-spoke design features each spoke splitting into two branches, creating a distinctive 10-element visual pattern. Factory finish was traditional silver paint. Standard BMW hub-centric design with 5x120 bolt pattern. Available in two size variants with progressive width increases. Commonly found on non-M E36, E46, and Z3 models as both standard and optional equipment.',
