VALUES (
  'bmw-style-2-36111179761',
  'BMW Style 2 [36111179761]',
  '36111179761, 36111129030',
  '[{"value":15,"unit":"inch","raw":"15 inch"}]',
  '[{"value":7,"unit":"J","raw":"7.0J"}]',
  '[{"value":"5x120"}]',
  '[{"value":"bmw"}]',
  '[{"value":"BMW - E24: 6-Series\nBMW - E32: 7-Series\nBMW - E34: 5-Series"}]',
  '[{"value":"72.6mm"}]',
  'ET20',
  '8.5 kg (18.7 lbs)',
  'Historic BMW Style 2 - The first BMW wheel to receive the official ''Style'' designation, marking the beginning of BMW''s systematic wheel numbering system. Originally called ''BMW-Styling'', this wheel became iconic as the ''Bottlecap'' due to its distinctive deep-dish multi-spoke design resembling a bottle cap. Produced from 1986-1994 exclusively for BMW''s flagship luxury models. Single size configuration only: 7.0Jx15 H2 ET20. Features unique 20-spoke turbine pattern with alternating long and short spokes creating a distinctive visual rhythm. Cast aluminum construction with durable BMW silver paint finish designed to complement period BMW exterior colors. Hollander interchange number 59170. Compatible with 195/65R15, 205/65R15, and 225/60R15 tire sizes. Historical significance as BMW''s design transition from anonymous wheel designs to the branded Style system that continues today. Exclusively manufactured for E24 6-Series (1986-1989), E32 7-Series (1986-1994), and E34 5-Series (1988-1994) models. Represents late-1980s BMW design language emphasizing luxury, functionality, and understated elegance.',
  'Standard BMW Silver Paint finish. Factory original finish only available in silver painted aluminum alloy.',
  '![[BMWStyle2.jpg]]',
  true
) ON CONFLICT (id) DO UPDATE SET
  wheel_title = EXCLUDED.wheel_title,
  part_numbers = EXCLUDED.part_numbers,
