  'ET20 (varies by application)',
  'Approximately 15-18 kg (varies by width)',
  'BMW Style 86 is a distinctive radial spoke split rim design introduced in the 1990s for the E36 generation. The wheel features a multi-piece construction with radial spokes connecting to a separate rim barrel. Originally designed to complement the aerodynamic lines of the E36 3 Series, it became available across multiple BMW platforms including the E46 3 Series, E39 5 Series, and Z3 roadster. The split rim design was popular in the 1990s and early 2000s, offering both visual appeal and performance benefits. Available in multiple widths to accommodate different vehicle applications and performance requirements. Exclusions include M3 and Compact models for certain variants. Production period spans from approximately 1990 through the early 2000s.',
  'Silver, Aluminum finish',
  '![[bmwstyle86.jpg]]',
  true
) ON CONFLICT (id) DO UPDATE SET
