VALUES (
  'bmw-style-180',
  'BMW Style 180',
  '36 11 6 768 562 (front 7.5J), 36 11 6 768 563 (rear 8J), 36 13 6 768 640 (hub cap)',
  '[{"value":18,"unit":"inch","raw":"18 inch"}]',
  '[{"value":7.5,"unit":"J","raw":"7.5J"},{"value":8,"unit":"J","raw":"8.0J"}]',
  '[{"value":"5x120"}]',
  '[{"value":"bmw"}]',
  '[{"value":"E87 1 Series (5-door hatchback 2004-2011)"},{"value":"E81 1 Series (3-door hatchback 2007-2012)"},{"value":"E82 1 Series Coupe (2007-2013)"},{"value":"E88 1 Series Convertible (2008-2013). Compatible with other BMW models with 5x120 bolt pattern and appropriate load rating."}]',
  '[{"value":"72.6mm - Standard BMW center bore diameter for E87/E81/E82/E88 1 Series models, ensuring proper hub-centric fitment."}]',
  'ET47 (front), ET49 (rear)',
  'Approximately 10-11 kg per wheel (varies by width: 7.5J front wheels lighter than 8.0J rear wheels). Lightweight cast aluminum construction reduces unsprung weight compared to steel alternatives.',
  'BMW Style 180 is a rare 7-spoke "Star Spoke" design wheel originally developed for the BMW E87 1 Series launch in September 2004. Part of the original E8x 1 Series generation (2004-2013) wheel lineup. Features distinctive asymmetric width configuration: 7.5J front and 8.0J rear for optimal handling balance. The star-like spoke pattern radiates from the center with seven evenly distributed spokes. Exclusively designed to complement the Chris Chapman-designed E87 bodywork under Chris Bangle''s design direction. Standard equipment on select E87/E81/E82/E88 models but compatible with other BMW models sharing 5x120 bolt pattern and appropriate load rating. The wheel incorporates BMW''s hub-centric design philosophy for precise fitment and reduced vibration. Manufactured using gravity casting process with machined spoke faces for durability and aesthetic appeal.',
  'Silver (standard OEM finish) - BMW''s traditional silver alloy wheel coating with clear protective topcoat. Paint code matches BMW''s OEM silver specifications for the E87 1 Series generation.',
  '![[bmwstyle180.jpg]]',
  true
) ON CONFLICT (id) DO UPDATE SET
  wheel_title = EXCLUDED.wheel_title,
  part_numbers = EXCLUDED.part_numbers,
  diameter_ref = EXCLUDED.diameter_ref,
