  '[{"value":"72.6mm"}]',
  'ET20, ET23, ET46',
  '8.36kg - 12.00kg',
  'BMW Style 25 is a classic 10-spoke design wheel specifically engineered for winter tire applications. Introduced in the mid-1990s during the E36 generation, this wheel style became a popular winter option across multiple BMW model lines due to its robust construction and practical design. The wheel features a multi-spoke pattern that provides excellent brake cooling while maintaining structural integrity in cold weather conditions. Different chassis applications required different offset specifications to accommodate varying suspension geometries and track widths. The E39 5 Series used a significantly lower offset (ET20) compared to the 3 Series applications (ET46) to accommodate its wider track. The E38 7 Series received the widest variant at 8.0J width with ET23 offset and correspondingly higher weight of 12.0kg. This wheel style represents BMW''s approach to combining functionality with classic styling during the 1990s era.',
  'Silver painted finish, Metallic silver',
  '![[bmwstyle25.jpg]]',
  true
) ON CONFLICT (id) DO UPDATE SET
